title: Relax, Meditate and Enjoy the Scenery at Barefoot Beach Preserve
text:
Updated: 2:50 p.m. Wednesday, Aug. 26, 2015 | Posted: 11:36 a.m. Tuesday, Aug. 25, 2015 Relax, Meditate and Enjoy the Scenery at Barefoot Beach Preserve In Partnership with VisitFlorida.com 
Barefoot Beach State Preserve, voted one of the best beaches in America, offers soft, fine sand, spectacular blue water, gentle, shallow surf and tons of seashells to collect. As one of the last undeveloped barrier islands in Florida, Barefoot Beach is home to protected species including gopher tortoises and ospreys. You might even spot a dolphin swimming off the coast.
